The Secretary of Health and Human Services, Kathleen Sebelius, has made a statement regarding the withdrawal of a proposed rate increase by California insurer, Anthem. This announcement is seen as good news for over 800,000 Californians who were at risk of facing significant rate hikes. Secretary Sebelius has expressed her concern for Americans who struggle with high health insurance premiums and states that the Affordable Care Act will ensure access to affordable and quality care. She emphasizes that the Department of Health and Human Services, along with the Office of Consumer Information and Insurance Oversight, will closely monitor the insurance industry and take action to prevent excessive premium increases.